"{\"uid\": \"english.aawsat.com-sports-5031306-gretchen-walsh-set-world-record-100-meter-butterfly-us-olympic-swimming-trials\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Gretchen Walsh set a world record in the women's 100-meter butterfly Saturday night, posting a time of 55.18 seconds in a semifinal heat at the US Olympic swimming trials.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gretchen Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 144, \"end\": 170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_Olympic_trials_(swimming)\", \"score\": 0.5975359342916774, \"rank\": 0.6735395189005082, \"text\": \"US Olympic swimming trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_Olympic_trials_(swimming)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_Olympic_trials_(swimming)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh was more than a half-second under world-record pace at the turn and held on to eclipse the mark of 55.48 set by Sweden's Sarah Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m at the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics.\", \"from\": 173, \"to\": 351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 291, \"end\": 297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999987178306617, \"rank\": 1.282170964941252e-06, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 300, \"end\": 314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"score\": 0.9999994657338511, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sarah Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I definitely was feeling it,\\\" said Walsh, who considers herself a stronger swimmer in the short-course pool.\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought I was dying.\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not know I was going that fast and, apparently, I took it out too fast.\\\"\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not to worry.\", \"from\": 567, \"to\": 580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh held her left hand over her mouth as she looked at the scoreboard in disbelief, a \\\"WR\\\" beside her name, The AP reported.\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 695, \"end\": 697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999959072738, \"rank\": 4.092625723309664e-09, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There has been a little bit of a buzz out there,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think going into tonight, like I knew it would take a (55) point-4 or I guess point-5, but I did not think I was going to do it tonight.\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 909, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just knew I wanted to go a fast time and now here I am - a world-record holder.\\\"\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 992, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year-old Walsh, a native of Nashville, Tennessee, who competes for the University of Virginia, still has some work to do to claim a spot on her first Olympic team.\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1040, \"end\": 1049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennessee_Titans\", \"score\": 0.6121683627316944, \"rank\": 0.6332691775853881, \"text\": \"Tennessee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennessee_Titans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennessee_Titans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the final Sunday night, she will face a strong field that includes Torri Huske, Regan Smith and Claire Curzan - all of them medalists from the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1236, \"end\": 1247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torri Huske\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\"}, {\"begin\": 1249, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.982606368001805e-38, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 1265, \"end\": 1278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Curzan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Claire Curzan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Curzan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Curzan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Walsh feels she can go even faster.\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1365, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I still have room to grow in that race,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The path to glory at the 2026 World Cup has now been laid out after the contenders discovered their tournament fate at Friday's draw ceremony in Washington which was dominated by Donald Trump.\", \"from\":